OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1780081925
OL,3,CHealth professionals challenge safety
OL,4,Cclaims by UK Sunbed Association
OL,6,FHealth professionals have debunked the
OL,7,Fidea that "tanned skin protects
OL,8,Fagainst sunburn", after a body which
OL,9,Frepresents sunbed salons in the UK
OL,10,Fsuggested it does on its website.
OL,12,FThe Sunbed Association is an industry
OL,13,Fvoice for tanning salons, which says
OL,14,Fit promotes "responsible UV tanning".
OL,16,FIn the FAQ section of its website, The
OL,17,FSunbed Association poses the question:
OL,18,F"Is it true there is no such thing as
OL,19,Fa safe tan?"
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1780081925
OL,3,CHealth professionals challenge safety
OL,4,Cclaims by UK Sunbed Association
OL,6,FUnderneath, it gives the answer: "No.
OL,7,FTanned skin protects against sunburn,
OL,8,Fthought to be the main cause of
OL,9,Fmelanoma.
OL,11,F"If you avoid getting sunburned, the
OL,12,Fbenefits of moderate sun exposure (see
OL,13,FVitamin D section) will far outweigh
OL,14,Fany risks."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1780081925
OL,3,CHealth professionals challenge safety
OL,4,Cclaims by UK Sunbed Association
OL,6,FFull Fact, an independent fact-
OL,7,Fchecking charity based in the UK, says
OL,8,Fthat the Sunbed Association's website
OL,9,Fhas "incorrect health advice on
OL,10,Ftanning, according to health
OL,11,Fauthorities and experts in the UK and
OL,12,Fworldwide".
OL,14,FCancer Research UK, which is also
OL,15,Fquoted in Full Fact's article, told
OL,16,FITV News: "There's no such thing as
OL,17,Fsafe tanning from UV radiation which
OL,18,Fis from the sun or sunbeds."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1780081925
OL,3,CHealth professionals challenge safety
OL,4,Cclaims by UK Sunbed Association
OL,6,FSophie Brooks, health information
OL,7,Fmanager at Cancer Research UK, said:
OL,8,F"A tan is a sign of skin damage and it
OL,9,Fdoesn't protect you from further
OL,10,Fdamage to your skin
OL,12,F"There's also no need to use sunbeds,
OL,13,Fsunbathe or risk sunburn to get enough
OL,14,FVitamin D."
OL,16,FFurthermore, President of The British
OL,17,FAssociation of Dermatologists Dr
OL,18,FTamara Griffiths also said that
OL,19,F"claims that there is such a thing as
OL,20,Fa 'safe tan' are not supported by the
OL,21,Fwider scientific evidence".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1780081925
OL,3,CHealth professionals challenge safety
OL,4,Cclaims by UK Sunbed Association
OL,6,FShe adds: "Tanned skin is the body's
OL,7,Fresponse to UV-induced damage.
OL,9,F"The tan develops only after harm has
OL,10,Falready occurred and provides minimal
OL,11,Fprotection, making it a sign of
OL,12,Fongoing skin damage rather than
OL,13,Fmeaningful defence against UV
OL,14,Fexposure."
OL,16,FThe Sunbed Association told ITV News
OL,17,Fin a statement:
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1780081925
OL,3,CHealth professionals challenge safety
OL,4,Cclaims by UK Sunbed Association
OL,6,F"Public discourse around UV exposure
OL,7,Fis often clouded by misconception and
OL,8,Fit is vital that we ground our
OL,9,Funderstanding in biological facts and
OL,10,Fresponsible practice.
OL,12,F"But let's be entirely clear,
OL,13,Fexcessive exposure to UV radiation can
OL,14,Flead to burning and burning must
OL,15,Falways be avoided.
OL,17,F"However, it is equally important to
OL,18,Funderstand that tanning itself is an
OL,19,Fentirely natural biological response."
OL,21,FHow can I protect my skin?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1780081925
OL,3,CHealth professionals challenge safety
OL,4,Cclaims by UK Sunbed Association
OL,6,FCancer Research UK advises that the
OL,7,Fbest way to protect your skin is to
OL,8,Fspend time in the shade, especially
OL,9,Fbetween 11am-3pm when the sun is
OL,10,Fstrongest.
OL,12,F"Cover up with clothing, especially
OL,13,Fyour shoulders, wear a hat and
OL,14,Fsunglasses and finally, use sunscreen
OL,15,Fwith at least SPF 30 and four or five
OL,16,Fstars," it says.
OL,18,F"Make sure you put plenty on and
OL,19,Freapply it regularly.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1780081925
OL,3,CHealth professionals challenge safety
OL,4,Cclaims by UK Sunbed Association
OL,6,F"Even if you've been sunburnt before,
OL,7,Fit's never too late to start
OL,8,Fprotecting your skin and reduce your
OL,9,Frisk of skin cancer."
OL,11,FSubscribe for free to our weekly
OL,12,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,13,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,14,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,16,FWhen should I visit a GP?
OL,18,FThe charity also advises speaking to
OL,19,Fyour GP if you notice "any unusual
OL,20,Fchanges to your skin, talk to your GP".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
